narratives.question_text: Use the space below to comment on questions 1-10, if you wish
comments: Nothing toshow..
The way Professor Brennan-Galvin teaches makes material which could be as boring as possible exciting.
Her course materials in every class are so informative and so easy to understand for me.

narratives.question_text: The things about this course most in need of improvement are:
comments: There's a certain lack of organization, although I believe that may be more due to the variety of students in the class rather than anything inherent about the class.
If I could, I want to go some field trips relating transportation issues.
Should arrange better class timing.In need of materials improvements, such as a more variant cases, engineering basics, theories, readings, etc.

narratives.question_text: What was the availability and quality of help you received of the instructor and TA?
comments: Temperance was incredibly available, and Professor Brennan-Galvin was available for a large part as well. They both helped a good amount.
No problem.

narratives.question_text: Discuss if you wish how this course fits into your overall program.
comments: I wish this class had a deeper discussions in resources usage and environmental impacts.

narratives.question_text: Why did you take this course?
comments: My focus is on urban environmental policies, and had heard that Professor Brennan-Galvin was an expert on that, particularly in transportation in developing countries.
I want to understand environmental problems comprehensively.

narratives.question_text: Did it live up to your expectations?
comments: It did, very much so. The class was also relaxed somewhat, so it was very enjoyable.
Yes.

narratives.question_text: Did you get out of it what you expected?
comments: Yes, although I didn't expect it to go into some of the areas it did.
Yes.

narratives.question_text: If yes, what were the advantages and disadvantages of the group work?
comments: The work was easier, but there wasn't really a chance to do present as a group.
Good point is for me to know what others consider about this issue. One regrettable point is not to have the presentation of this result.
Works well. Had a good time in discussing the project.

narratives.question_text: For students taking this course, what advice would you give them?
comments: Stay on top of the work, which is very little, and don't worry too much about it.
